This directory contains the distributed version of MNDO2020.

Date: 18 May 2022.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

Files:
README        This file.
MNDO2020.f    Main program for MNDO2020.
LIMIT.f90     Parameters defining maximum array sizes.
configure.ac  Configure script for the generation of the Makefile's.
Makefile.am   Makefile templates for the generation of the Makefile's.
mndo99.doc    Program documentation (out-dated, revision required).
mndo2020.txt  Input description.

Subdirectories:
2020/         General MNDO source code.
BIN/          Latest precompiled binary.
BLAS/         Source code for BLAS routines.
CGDMS/        Source code for conjugate gradient density matrix search.
DFTB/         Source code for density functional based tight binding.
ES/           Source code for spin-flip (extended) CIS excited states.
GUGACI/       Source code for GUGA-CI routines.
HDLCOPT/      Source code for HDLC optimizer.
LAPACK/       Source code for LAPACK routines.
MACHINE/      Source code of machine-dependent and dummy routines.
PS/           Source code for analytic derivatives and NMR.
PSEX/         Source code for surface crossing/hopping methods.
SCOSMO/       Source code for smooth COSMO solvation model.
SPARSE/       Source code for sparse DMS.
VB/           Source code for valence bond module.
testjobs/     Standard MNDO test jobs (formatted input).
testkeys/     Standard MNDO test jobs (keyword input).
testmopac6/   Test jobs from MOPAC(6.0).
testps/       Test jobs for analytic derivatives and NMR.
testes/       Test jobs for spin-flip (extended) CIS excited states.
testguga/     Test jobs for GUGA-CI module.
testhdlc/     Test jobs for HDLC optimizer.
testpsex/     Test jobs for surface crossing/hopping methods.
testlindir/   Test jobs for direct density matrix search (full matrices).
testsparse/   Test jobs for sparse conjugate gradient density matrix search.
testscosmo/   Test jobs for smooth COSMO solvation model.
testvb/       Test jobs for VB module.
testdftb/     Test jobs for density functional based tight binding.

See READ_ME files in these subdirectories for further information.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

The installation and validation of MNDO is described in the program
documentation (mndo99.doc, section 3).
